<refsect2 id="tracker-module-metadata-utils-get-data" role="function">
<title>tracker_module_metadata_utils_get_data ()</title>
<indexterm zone="tracker-module-metadata-utils-get-data"><primary>tracker_module_metadata_utils_get_data</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="TrackerModuleMetadata">TrackerModuleMetadata</link>* tracker_module_metadata_utils_get_data
                                                        (<link linkend="GFile">GFile</link> *file);</programlisting>
<para>
Returns a <link linkend="TrackerModuleMetadata"><type>TrackerModuleMetadata</type></link> filled in with all the
metadata that could be extracted for the given file.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>file</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> A <link linkend="GFile"><type>GFile</type></link>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> A newly created <link linkend="TrackerModuleMetadata"><type>TrackerModuleMetadata</type></link>, or <link linkend="NULL:CAPS"><literal>NULL</literal></link> if the file is not found.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="tracker-module-metadata-utils-get-text" role="function">
<title>tracker_module_metadata_utils_get_text ()</title>
<indexterm zone="tracker-module-metadata-utils-get-text"><primary>tracker_module_metadata_utils_get_text</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="gchar">gchar</link>*              tracker_module_metadata_utils_get_text
                                                        (<link linkend="GFile">GFile</link> *file);</programlisting>
<para>
Gets the text from <parameter>file</parameter>, if the file is considered as
containing plain text, it will be extracted, else this function
will resort to the installed text filters for the file MIME type.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>file</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> A <link linkend="GFile"><type>GFile</type></link>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> A newly allocated string containing the file text, or <link linkend="NULL:CAPS"><literal>NULL</literal></link>.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>

</refsect1>



